        <num>CC 601</num>
        <heading>601.  Removal of improvements</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 601.  Removal of improvements
The usufructuary may remove all improvements he has made, subject to the obligation of restoring the property to its former condition.  He may not claim reimbursement from the owner for improvements that he does not remove or that cannot be removed.</p>
        </content>
